              <description><![CDATA[•    Lighting your workload despite continuous assessment<br />
•    Don’t be lead by the technology, use it in a way that is meaningful for you<br />
•    Important to integrate the technology, rather than bolt it on<br />
•    Dual paradigms: technologies with amazing affordances but a teacher approach which is outdated and teacher-focused<br />
•    Why bother investing the time? Marking loads of assessments, tired of handling loads of lab books and scripts, facilitate more group work with less administration, means of providing individual feedback <br />
