                    <item>
              <title>Learners reshaping learning landscapes: new directions for old challenges?</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/550</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/550</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Designing and integrating ICT enhanced learning and teaching</strong></p>
<p>There are numerous process modes and frameworks developed</p>
<p>to scaffold the process of designing and/or adapting curricula</p>
<p>to exploit the under utilised potential of ICT</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Issues</em></p>
<ol>
    <li>Pragmatic issues</li>
    <li>Design models&nbsp; are too mechanical</li>
    <li>Gap between teachers hopes and educational outcomes (Goodyear)</li>
    <li>Design quality varies</li>
    <li>There is still a tendency for technology to drive</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>The ICTELT process model</em></p>
<p>It has an iteractive structure that remains flexible enough for practitioners to</p>
<p>blend the approach of their choice while also encouraging the alignment of pedagogical</p>
<p>perspectives and practice. The guided questions and scaffolding are designed to form a basis</p>
<p>for collaborative discussion of design choices, ICT tool selection, and the complexity</p>
<p>of incorporating a range of pedagogical apraohces with a variety of tools.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Resources</em>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.netvibes.com/hazelowen#General">Online blog</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.slideshare.net/hazelowendmc/learners-reshaping-learning-landscapes-owen-presentation">Presentation on slideshare<br />
</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://efest2008collaboratingbydesign.pbwiki.com/">Collaborating by design wiki site <br />
</a></p>
<p>(Username: efest2008, password: efest2008)</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://hazelowen.vox.com">VOX</a></p>]]></description>
